text: William McCormick (1801 – 12 June 1878) was an Irish Conservative politician. McCormick was elected as Member of Parliament (MP) for Londonderry City at a by-election in 1860 but stood down at the next general election in 1865. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1801 births Category:1878 deaths Category:Irish Conservative Party MPs Category:Members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for County Londonderry constituencies (1801–1922) Category:UK MPs 1859–1865
